<subSubSection id="BB16F641096363DB07025A9419BB7DA8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="79909FB0CE0D8BEDC4E4E0205764F0D7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F07A886F0D2DA2F3E027D3DAE1F60EF9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="98739DEEE53EB774941AA23360A99F51" authorityName="Tochihara and Hosoya" authorityYear="2022" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Lachnaceae" genus="Erioscyphella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Erioscyphella paralushanensis" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="paralushanensis">
<emphasis id="96AA2B47EB3369860A1EE09673683B3E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Erioscyphella paralushanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="5016239B99CB35D9AB8F9412E1742578" genus="E." lsidName="E. lushanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="lushanensis">
<emphasis id="C6836F7CA4206E8C7FCAD23450587A47" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. lushanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having red hairs (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B208B1E5FA54F9789B7C22B7E96CB720" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Erioscyphella paralushanensis TNS-F- 61920 (Holotype) A apothecia B pure culture on PDA (NBRC 114468) C ascus D ascal pore iodine reactions D 1 MLZ (faintly +) without 3 % KOH pretreatment D 2 MLZ (+) with 3 % KOH pretreatment D 3 IKI (+) without 3 % KOH pretreatment E paraphysis F ascospores G ectal excipular cells H marginal section of an apothecium generating hairs I hairs with red resinous materials J apical amorphous materials of hairs. Mounted in CB / LA (C, E-J), MLZ (D 1, D 2), IKI (D 3). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 10 µm (C-J)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.87.73082.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/643420" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">13I</figureCitation>
) and the ectal excipulum composed of well-developed rectangular cells in common (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="23E59BD11E79930F1500B09461FF6B8A" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Erioscyphella paralushanensis TNS-F- 61920 (Holotype) A apothecia B pure culture on PDA (NBRC 114468) C ascus D ascal pore iodine reactions D 1 MLZ (faintly +) without 3 % KOH pretreatment D 2 MLZ (+) with 3 % KOH pretreatment D 3 IKI (+) without 3 % KOH pretreatment E paraphysis F ascospores G ectal excipular cells H marginal section of an apothecium generating hairs I hairs with red resinous materials J apical amorphous materials of hairs. Mounted in CB / LA (C, E-J), MLZ (D 1, D 2), IKI (D 3). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 10 µm (C-J)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.87.73082.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/643420" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">13H</figureCitation>
, Fig. 
<figureCitation id="059030F690BEEDD31451C4453825F4F8" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Erioscyphella paralushanensis TNS-F- 61920 (Holotype) A apothecia B vertical section of an apothecium C expansion of an vertical section of an apothecium D asci E hairs F ectal excipulum G paraphyses H ascospores." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.87.73082.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/643421" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">14C</figureCitation>
, and Fig. 
<figureCitation id="88FD3479E9543EF85DEA61811C9B8D88" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Erioscyphella paralushanensis TNS-F- 61920 (Holotype) A apothecia B vertical section of an apothecium C expansion of an vertical section of an apothecium D asci E hairs F ectal excipulum G paraphyses H ascospores." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.87.73082.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/643421" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">14F</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="06CD5E09FA6DE00AD69A3034EABBB0ED" author="Zhuang, WY" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="429 - 438" refId="B79" refString="Zhuang, WY, Wang, Z, 1998a. Some new species and new records of discomycetes in China. VIII. Mycotaxon 66: 429 - 438" title="Some new species and new records of discomycetes in China. VIII." volume="66" year="1998 a">Zhuang and Wang 1998a</bibRefCitation>
). Compared with 
<taxonomicName id="9F76CE8BB90CCDCAC02ED7F88E4856C9" genus="E." lsidName="E. lushanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="lushanensis">
<emphasis id="E3D65858D73F7307EFE5891DAA553875" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. lushanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EB96826042DECA24FF89BA9B98A3C25E" genus="E." lsidName="E. paralushanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="paralushanensis">
<emphasis id="B9A18EF914A0B6744863C977C2D0BF1F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. paralushanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has slightly larger asci, ascospores and hairs. Red guttules in ascospores were observed only in 
<taxonomicName id="840668500A0C294B3EBA4E99B3565CD1" genus="E." lsidName="E. paralushanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="paralushanensis">
<emphasis id="B5752D50BCAA3CAA7D193E3FEB3863E4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. paralushanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9BA659919CFA9A73F5F75850CAE5C70B" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Erioscyphella paralushanensis TNS-F- 61920 (Holotype) A apothecia B pure culture on PDA (NBRC 114468) C ascus D ascal pore iodine reactions D 1 MLZ (faintly +) without 3 % KOH pretreatment D 2 MLZ (+) with 3 % KOH pretreatment D 3 IKI (+) without 3 % KOH pretreatment E paraphysis F ascospores G ectal excipular cells H marginal section of an apothecium generating hairs I hairs with red resinous materials J apical amorphous materials of hairs. Mounted in CB / LA (C, E-J), MLZ (D 1, D 2), IKI (D 3). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 10 µm (C-J)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.87.73082.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/643420" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">13F</figureCitation>
). In this study, we proposed the present fungus as a new species, because species delimitation analyses based on ITS sequences strongly supported that 
<taxonomicName id="E4D7E3DCE4ECF1E274CFDB5B52174333" genus="E." lsidName="E. paralushanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="paralushanensis">
<emphasis id="A394FB0CA7E5DE20C4C159F91E005F8E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. paralushanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is different from 
<taxonomicName id="B14F6F8F5460F9138BB559DF851FD000" genus="E." lsidName="E. lushanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="lushanensis">
<emphasis id="18C0F1218C719518A360EA0D27249D10" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. lushanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="99A46706E0B1564E1824D419B08BEA9C" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Species delimitation analyses using ITS sequences of Erioscyphella and its potential members. Clusters based on UNITE SH at 3 % and 1.5 % threshold values at UNITE v 8.2, VSEARCH at 97 % and 98.5 % threshold values, ASAP, GMYC, and PTP are displayed. Schematic phylogenetic relationships are shown using the ultrametric tree constructed for the GMYC analysis. The taxon names shown on the tree branches follow the results of the present study." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.87.73082.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/643410" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
